  "text": "Firefox TLS Handshake Chain: Networking Layer to Crypto Layer\n\n1. NETWORKING LAYER - HTTPS Connection Initiation\n   File: netwerk/protocol/http/nsHttpConnection.cpp\n   Class: nsHttpConnection\n   \n   The nsHttpConnection class manages HTTP(S) connections. When an HTTPS connection is required, it sets up a TLS socket and initiates the TLS handshake through the TlsHandshaker component.\n\n2. HTTP PROTOCOL LAYER - TLS Handshake Driver\n   File: netwerk/protocol/http/TlsHandshaker.cpp\n   Class: TlsHandshaker\n   Key Function: TlsHandshaker::DriveHandshake() (line 216-217)\n   \n   TlsHandshaker orchestrates the TLS handshake process. It calls DriveHandshake() on the nsITLSSocketControl interface (implemented by NSSSocketControl), which drives the actual handshake on the NSS side.\n\n3. SOCKET LAYER - TLS Socket Control\n   File: security/manager/ssl/NSSSocketControl.cpp\n   Class: NSSSocketControl\n   Key Functions:\n   - ActivateSSL() (line 372): Sets up and activates the SSL layer\n   - DriveHandshake() (line 241-244): Drives the TLS handshake state machine\n   \n   NSSSocketControl implements nsITLSSocketControl and manages the TLS socket state. It interfaces between Necko's socket layer and NSS's crypto layer.\n\n4. SSL/TLS BRIDGE LAYER - NSS I/O Layer Integration\n   File: security/manager/ssl/nsNSSIOLayer.cpp\n   Class: nsSSLIOLayerHelpers (defined in nsNSSIOLayer.h)\n   Key Functions:\n   - HandshakeCallback() (line 982): Called when NSS completes the handshake\n   - SSL_HandshakeCallback() setup (line 1278): Registers NSS handshake callback\n   \n   nsNSSIOLayer provides the bridge between Necko's socket abstraction and NSS's SSL/TLS implementation. The HandshakeCallback handles completion of the NSS handshake and updates Firefox's TLS state.\n\n5. NSS SOCKET LAYER - Socket Operations\n   File: security/nss/lib/ssl/sslsock.c\n   Key Functions:\n   - ssl_Recv() (line 3234-3237): Receives data over SSL socket\n   - ssl_Send() (referenced in ops table at line 3807): Sends data over SSL socket\n   - Socket operations table: maps PR_CALLBACK functions for socket I/O\n   \n   sslsock.c implements the socket-level operations for NSS SSL connections, translating between NSPR (Netscape Portable Runtime) socket calls and NSS crypto operations.\n\n6. NSS SECURE SOCKET OPERATIONS - Connection Establishment\n   File: security/nss/lib/ssl/sslsecur.c\n   Key Functions:\n   - ssl_SecureConnect() (line 691-694): Establishes secure connection and initiates handshake\n   - SSL_HandshakeCallback() (line 288-291): Registers callback for handshake completion\n   - SSL_ResetHandshake(), SSL_ForceHandshake(): Handshake control functions\n   \n   sslsecur.c implements high-level SSL/TLS secure connection operations, managing the handshake state machine and connection lifecycle.\n\n7. NSS TLS HANDSHAKE - Cryptographic Handshake\n   File: security/nss/lib/ssl/ssl3con.c\n   Key Functions:\n   - ssl3_SendClientHello() (line 5504-5507): Sends TLS ClientHello message\n   - ssl3_HandleRecord() (line 13720-13723): Processes received TLS records\n   - ssl3_HandleNonApplicationData(): Handles handshake and control messages\n   \n   ssl3con.c implements the actual TLS 1.0-1.2 protocol handshake, including record processing, message handling, and cipher suite negotiation. This is where the cryptographic operations occur.\n\nHANDSHAKE FLOW:\n1. nsHttpConnection initiates HTTPS connection\n2. TlsHandshaker::DriveHandshake() is called periodically to drive the handshake\n3. NSSSocketControl::DriveHandshake() calls ActivateSSL() to set up NSS layer\n4. nsNSSIOLayer sets up the NSS I/O layer and registers SSL_HandshakeCallback()\n5. NSS ssl_SecureConnect() begins the TLS handshake\n6. ssl3_SendClientHello() sends the initial handshake message\n7. ssl3_HandleRecord() processes server responses\n8. HandshakeCallback() in nsNSSIOLayer is invoked when handshake completes\n9. Connection is now ready for HTTP/HTTPS communication"
}

